# {{projectName}} — GitHub Copilot instructions

Project-scoped rules for Copilot. For cross-tool context see `AGENTS.md`.

## Workspace-centric skills

This is a NONoise multi-repo workspace. The `.claude/skills/` tree lives at
the workspace root. Open this directory in your editor and Copilot will
find every skill. Sub-repos under `repos/` are separate git repositories
and do NOT carry their own skill tree. If you need skills inside a
specific sub-repo, copy `.claude/` manually.

## Entry point — Polly

This project ships with **Polly**, the NONoise SDLC orchestrator. Whenever the developer
is unsure what to do next, or asks "start polly" / "avvia polly" / "orchestrate this
project", read `.claude/skills/polly/SKILL.md` and follow its decision tree.

If the file `.nonoise/POLLY_START.md` exists in the project root, your FIRST action this
session is to invoke Polly, then delete `.nonoise/POLLY_START.md` so it doesn't re-trigger.

## Conventions

- Follow the existing code style in the file you're editing.
- Write tests alongside implementations.
- Use clear, descriptive names.

## Available skills (cross-tool)

This project contains a library of AI skills in `.claude/skills/`. The skills are plain
markdown and apply to every AI tool, including Copilot. When the user's task matches the
description of one of these skills, open the corresponding `SKILL.md` file and follow its
instructions.

Installed skills:

**Orchestrator** — `polly`

**Requirements & discovery** — `requirements-ingest`, `bmad-agent-analyst`,
`bmad-advanced-elicitation`

**Architecture & validation** — `arch-brainstorm`, `arch-decision`, `quint-fpf`,
`bmad-agent-architect`

**Sprint & implementation** — `sprint-manifest`, `atr`

**Brownfield** — `reverse-engineering`

**Ops & observability** — `ops-skill-builder`, `observability-debug`

**Integrations** — `spec-to-workitem`, `playwright-cli`, `frontend-design`,
`bmad-agent-ux-designer`, `bmad-agent-tech-writer`

**Generators** — `vscode-config-generator`, `docs-md-generator`, `design-md-generator`

**Utility** — `skill-finder`

**Superpowers (vendored from `obra/superpowers`)** — read these when the
workflow calls for them (Polly engages them during the SDLC loop):
`superpowers:brainstorming`, `superpowers:writing-plans`,
`superpowers:executing-plans`, `superpowers:test-driven-development`,
`superpowers:verification-before-completion`, `superpowers:systematic-debugging`,
`superpowers:subagent-driven-development`, `superpowers:dispatching-parallel-agents`,
`superpowers:using-git-worktrees`, `superpowers:finishing-a-development-branch`,
`superpowers:requesting-code-review`, `superpowers:receiving-code-review`,
`superpowers:writing-skills`, `superpowers:using-superpowers`

Bundled skills live at `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`. Vendored superpowers
live at `.claude/skills/superpowers/<name>/SKILL.md`. Open each folder's
`SKILL.md` for triggers and workflow.

