## polly

If the file `.nonoise/POLLY_START.md` exists, your FIRST action this session is to
invoke Polly — read `.claude/skills/polly/SKILL.md` and follow its decision tree fully —
then delete `.nonoise/POLLY_START.md` so the next session does not re-trigger.

Otherwise, invoke Polly when the user says "start polly" / "avvia polly" / "run polly" /
"orchestrate this project", or when they seem lost ("where do I start?", "which skill
for X?", "what's next?"). Polly is the conductor across the SDLC — it decides which
specialist skill to engage next.
